Mahindra to Sell Holiday Unit Stake Valued at 2.2 Billion Rupees

-- B y   P o o j a   T h a k u r
-- 
2011-09-15T06:58:27Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-15/mahindra-to-sell-holiday-unit-stake-valued-at-2-2-billion-rupees.html
Mahindra & Mahindra Ltd. (MM) ,  India â€™s
biggest maker of sport-utility vehicles and tractors, will sell
a stake valued at 2.24 billion rupees ($47 million) in unit
Mahindra Holidays and Resorts India Ltd. to comply with local
public shareholding norms.  The rules require companies with less than 25 percent
public stake to reach the threshold by June 2013, Mahindra &
Mahindra said in a statement to the stock exchange. The company,
which owns 83.09 percent of the holiday unit, said it will sell
8.09 percent in one or more lots through exchanges.  Mahindra Holidays rose 3.2 percent to 328.75 rupees as of
12:09 p.m. in Mumbai trading, snapping five-day 9.5 percent
decline. Mahindra & Mahindra climbed 0.4 percent to 796.95
rupees.  To contact the reporter on this story:
